headline: Financial data firm FactSet's Q3 profit falls as clients curb spending
summary: Financial data firm FactSet on Monday reported a fall in third-quarter profit, pressured by slower client spending amid ongoing macroeconomic uncertainty. WHY IT IS IMPORTANT Trade policy uncertainty under the Trump administration has prompted investors and clients to take a wait-and-see approach, dampening deal flow and demand for market-related products at FactSet. BY THE NUMBERS The company's organic annual subscription value (ASV) — which indicates the revenue potential for the next 12 months from subscription services — rose 4.5% to $2.3 billion during the quarter.
